                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/694.]</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 21, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President announced by proclamation this afternoon his retirement from office
                    July 1, 1914, and elections are set for May, 1914. Amnesty guaranties and
                    release of political prisoners decreed; also return of citizens from abroad;
                    foreigners not mentioned. The entire Cabinet will resign, the President will
                    return all resignations, after which the Minister of War, for patriotic reasons,
                    will decline to serve any longer. The Minister’s brother will also resign.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
